        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 28 at 5:58PM EDT until June 28 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS Pittsburgh PA</headline>
        <description>At 558 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near New Stanton,
or 11 miles south of Jeannette, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Greensburg, Latrobe, Monessen, Clairton, Donora, Mount Pleasant,
Monongahela, Charleroi, McChesneytown-Loyalhanna, Youngwood, West
Newton, Lawson Heights, New Stanton, North Belle Vernon, Wickerham
Manor-Fisher, Calumet-Norvelt, North Charleroi, Lincoln,
Lynnwood-Pricedale and Sutersville.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. This storm is capable of producing damaging winds.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning is one of nature's leading killers. Remember, if you can
hear thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
